    "client_msg_id": "362ad882-7007-49d1-a676-266770eaa6e5",
    "type": "message",
    "text": "Perhaps there's insight to be found in how compression and abstraction compate.  For instance in LZMA and similar, the sequences that get compressed are very much tied to the data.  There's a general rule for finding sequences, but the ones you use are specific to the data.  Likewise, you usually learn that an abstraction is poor when it overfits a few use-cases but can't be used most of the time.",
